BEGIN_TEXT
Evaluate the exact value of each limit.  Decimal answers are not allowed.  (Hint: look at the graph of \(\tan^{-1} (x) \).)
$BR
$BR
(a)  \( \lim\limits_{ x \rightarrow +\infty } \tan^{-1} (x) = \) \{ans_rule(5) \}
$BR
$BR
(b)  \( \lim\limits_{ x \rightarrow -\infty } \tan^{-1} (x) = \) \{ans_rule(5) \}
END_TEXT
ANS(Compute("pi/2")->cmp(studentsMustReduceFractions=>1));
ANS(Compute("-pi/2")->cmp(studentsMustReduceFractions=>1));


